curam.util.common.domain

Interface DomainOptions

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DomainPlugIn, PlugIn
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ClientDomainOptions, curam.util.common.domain.DefaultMutableDomainOptions

    public interface DomainOptions
extends DomainPlugIn
    An interface to access the options that can be specified for a domain in the UML model. This is intentionally a simple interface to allow it to remain constant if new options are added. The options are a type of domain plug-in that is "built in" to the infrastructure and not configured per domain.

    • Method Detail

      • getOption

        java.lang.String getOption(java.lang.String optionName)
        Gets the value of the named option. Options are expressed in the model documentation as name/value pairs.
        Parameters:
        optionName - The name of the option as used in the UML model.
        Returns:
        The value of the option, or null if the option is not set.

      • getOptionNames

        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getOptionNames()
        Gets a set of all of the option names. The set is not mutable, but may be backed by the options store and subject to change.
        Returns:
        The set of names.
